snippet: Tiger Woods had a birdie putt on every hole and made 10 of them on Friday to tie his own course record at Sherwood in Thousand Oaks, Calif., and take a three-shot lead in the World Challenge.
abstract: Tiger Woods takes second-round lead in the World Challenge at Sherwood in Thousand Oaks, Calif, tying his own course record; other golf news noted.
lead_paragraph: Tiger Woods had a birdie putt on every hole and made 10 of them on Friday to tie his own course record at Sherwood in Thousand Oaks, Calif., and take a three-shot lead in the World Challenge.

headline.main: Woods Cards a 62 to Lead World Challenge
